# Git Workflow

## Repository

- **GitHub:** https://github.com/BetterBloodInc/better-blood-web-app
- **Default branch:** `main`
- The git repo lives inside `better-blood-web-app/` (not the parent workspace).
- Always run git commands from the `better-blood-web-app/` directory.

## Workspace layout

The Cursor workspace may be rooted at a parent directory (e.g. `betterblood/`), but the `.git` repo is inside `better-blood-web-app/`. When committing or pushing, **always `cd` into `better-blood-web-app/` first**.

```
betterblood/                  ← workspace root (no git remote)
└── better-blood-web-app/     ← git repo, origin → GitHub
```

## Branching

- Work on `main` by default.
- Push with `git push` (upstream is `origin/main`).
- For feature work, branch off `main` and open a PR back to `main`.

## Committing

- Stage with `git add -A` (or selectively).
- Write concise commit messages: summary line + optional bullet list of changes.
- Never commit `.env`, credentials, or secrets.

## Pushing

```bash
cd better-blood-web-app
git add -A
git commit -m "Your message"
git push
```

## Important

- Do NOT add a remote or push from the parent `betterblood/` directory.
- Do NOT push to a `master` branch — the default is `main`.
